reviews.review_text:
Sweet, sweet soundboard! Thank God for the malfunctioning ultrabox!  I love pure soundboard recordings.  Haven't heard one since the '85 or maybe early '86 shows.  I don't know why people like crowd noise?  We're here to listen to the Dead right?

I like to check out the conversations between songs.  It adds the human element back into the band joking around with each other.  Put your headphones on and crank it up!

Anyway, very good sounding show after the ultrabox is shut off at the second verse of Minglewood.  Not the best playing I've ever heard from the band though.  Not particularly "jammy".

Five stars for the great recording, three for the playing.

12-28-87 Nice show. Perfect sound after the ultrabox is shut off one minute into Minglewood.Thanks Charlie. I think alot of people like matrix recordings because it makes them feel like they are there. I can take 'em or leave 'em.
Of course,I was there! 2nd nite of 4. Once Healy's ultrabox is shut off{Minglewood}It all takes form.Thank you Charlie Miller.#dontletgo
